cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.DM, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the computation of depth distribution of a set of axis aligned boxes, which is a problem in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The algorithmic techniques used in the paper to compute the depth distribution involve data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DB (Databases) - The motivation for the problem comes from the analysis of range queries in databases. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with combinatorial and discrete geometric problems related to the intersection graph formed by the boxes. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the worst-case complexity of the algorithm for computing the depth distribution.
